Blake, 71, faces life in prison if convicted of killing Bakley.
who considered himself a streetwise tough guy -- into marriage by getting pregnant.
Blake killed Bakley, the prosecutor said, when he couldn't find a way to avoid marrying her or to take custody of their baby.
Samuels cautioned the jury not to judge Blake based on Bakley's past.
Schwartzbach argued Thursday that Blake had been willing to put up with Bakley for the sake of their daughter.
Schwartzbach reminded jurors that Gary McLarty testified that Blake never directly asked to kill his wife.
But Samuels told jurors that if Blake really wanted to protect his wife he never would have left her alone in a car parked on a dark street.
